## URGENT — test failures unearthed

The most recent commit `7a9b434b` added `-UNDEBUG` to
`libopendkim/tests/CMakeLists.txt` so that `assert()` actually runs in
the test binaries.  Until then the entire libopendkim test suite was
compiled with `-DNDEBUG`, which turned every `assert()` into `((void)0)`
and made the tests trivially "pass" without checking anything.

After the fix, `ctest` reports **26 of 175 tests failing**.  These are
real pre-existing bugs (either in libopendkim or in the test fixtures)
that were silently masked.  Examples seen so far:

  - t-test102: `dkim_sig_geterror(sig) == DKIM_SIGERROR_MBSFAILED` —
    must-be-signed handling does not surface the expected error code.

