## Remaining warning categories (in order)

### 4. -Wunused-function (1 warning)

    opendkim/opendkim.c:3912: dkimf_checkfsnode defined but not used

Grep the tree for callers; if dead, delete the function and any
companions.  If gated behind a `#ifdef` that's currently off, wrap
the function in the same `#ifdef`.

### 5. -Wunused-parameter (44 warnings)

In callback stubs that must match a function-pointer signature, the
project pattern is `(void) param;` casts at the top of the body —
see commit 56b5a27d.  Do not change the signature.

### 6. -Wsign-compare (113 warnings)

`int` vs `size_t` comparisons.  These sometimes hide off-by-one or
signed wrap.  Look at the actual range of values:
  - If the count is genuinely `size_t`, change the loop variable's
    type.
  - Only cast when the producer really returns `int`.

### 7. -Wpointer-sign (217 warnings)

`u_char *` (libopendkim API — DKIM byte data) vs `char *` (daemon —
printable strings).  Most warnings are at the boundary.  Prefer narrow
casts at call sites over flipping API signatures (touching `dkim.h` is
high-blast-radius).  **Stop and report if a fix needs an API signature
change — that decision belongs to the user.**

## Workflow notes (carried over)

- This is a CMake project, not autotools.  Build with
  `cd build && make -j$(nproc) 2>&1 | tee ../build.log`.
- One logical fix per commit, matching the existing "Fix: …" style.
- Group mechanically-identical fixes into one commit; keep different
  bug shapes separate.
- **Bug fixes get their own commits** — do not bundle a real
  behavioural fix with surrounding cleanup, even within one file.
  Example from this session: the `dkimf_xs_delheader` idx-arg fix
  (d8a9beaa) was committed alone, separate from the cleanup commit
  (e27bab95) that touched the same file.
- No `Co-Authored-By: Claude` lines on commits.
- Don't commit unrelated dirty files — `PROMPT_WARNINGS` (this file)
  is left dirty by the user and must not be folded into a fix commit.
- After each commit, rebuild and confirm the warning count for that
  category dropped by the expected amount.
- Skip the 7 -Wformat-truncation warnings — verified safe in the
  prior session (opendkim.c:9536/11286, opendkim-db.c:1689 are
